:CONFLICT_BANK :measures :OriginalAnswerRatio ;
    :contextText "We measure the Original Answer Ratio (OAR)" .

:CONFLICT_BANK :measures :CounterAnswerRatio ;
    :contextText "and the Counter Answer Ratio (CAR) to assess model performance" .

:MemorizationRatio :relatedTo "MR=OAR/(OAR+CAR)" ;
    :contextText "MR=OAR OAR +CAR(1)" .

:MemorizationRatio :measures :RelianceOnParametricMemory ;
    :contextText "where higher memorization ratios indicate greater reliance on parametric memory" .

:MemorizationRatio :relatedTo :AdoptionOfConflictingKnowledge ;
    :contextText "while lower ratios suggest more adoption of the constructed conflicting knowledge." .

:EvaluationProtocol :uses :ChoiceProbabilities ;
    :contextText "The model then generates probabilities for the tokens “(A)”, “(B)”, “(C)” and “(D)”. The option with the highest probability is selected as the predicted answer." .

:Experiments :randomize :EvidenceOrder ;
    :contextText "The order of evidence is randomized in all experiments to avoid any influence of sequence on the results." .

:LLMs :achievesScore "MR below 50% when only conflicting external evidence" ;
    :contextText "all models exhibit memorization ratios below 50%, indicating that models are highly receptive to external evidence when it is the only evidence available" .

:LLMs :achievesScore "MR over 50% with both default and conflicting evidence" ;
    :contextText "all LLMs demonstrate significantly higher memorization ratios (over 50%) when parametric memory is also provided as evidence." .

:LLMs :shows :HigherSensitivityToTemporalAndSemanticConflicts ;
    :contextText "all models exhibit a lower MRin temporal and semantic conflicts compared to misinformation conflicts" .

:LLaMA2-70B :achievesScore "MR 7.77% (temporal) and 3.73% (semantic) vs 9.45% (misinformation)" ;
    :contextText "in the LLAMA2-70B model, the MRfor temporal and semantic conflicts is lower than those for misinformation conflicts (i.e., 7.77% & 3.73% v.s. 9.45%)." .

:LargerModels :relatedTo :IncreasedSusceptibilityToConflictingKnowledge ;
    :contextText "These observations suggest that larger models exhibit increased susceptibility to conflicting knowledge" .

:LLaMA2_Series :shows :MRDecreaseWithSize ;
    :contextText "in the LLaMA2 series, the MRconsistently decreases as the parameters increase from 7B to 13B to 70B" .

:LLaMA2_Series :achievesScore "MR reductions of 5.12% and 6.37%" ;
    :contextText "with reductions of 5.12% and 6.37% in an average of three conflict causes, respectively." .

:LLaMA2-7B :achievesScore "MR 56.44% when conflicting memory is placed later" ;
    :contextText "in the LLaMA2 series, when conflicting memory is placed later in the sequence, the 7B model has a MRof 56.44%" .

:LLaMA2-70B :achievesScore "MR 38.97% when conflicting memory is placed later" ;
    :contextText "while the 70B model’s MRdrops to 38.97%." .

:EvidenceOrder :resultIn :ImpactOnConflictingKnowledgeHandling ;
    :contextText "This phenomenon highlights the importance of considering evidence order to mitigate the impact of conflicting knowledge in future retrieval-augmented models." .

:LLAMA2-7B :achievesScore "OAR decrease 41.5% at 2:1 conflicts" ;
    :contextText "Even with only one-third (2:1 ratio of default to conflicting data) of the data being conflicting, these models exhibit substantial declines in OAR, with decreases of 41.5% and 37.6%, respectively." .

:Mistral-7B :achievesScore "OAR decrease 37.6% at 2:1 conflicts" ;
    :contextText "with decreases of 41.5% and 37.6%, respectively." .

:ExternalDefaultEvidence :improves :RobustnessAgainstInternalConflicts ;
    :contextText "when we prepend the original default evidence to the question, we find that models maintain their original performance, choosing the default answer regardless of the amount of conflicting data introduced." .

:RetrievedOrToolAssistedMethods :improves :MitigationOfInternalConflicts ;
    :contextText "leveraging retrieved or tool-assisted methods to access correct and relevant knowledge can effectively mitigate the adverse effects of internal conflicts on model performance." .

:InternalConflicts :resultIn :IncreasedRelianceOnExternalEvidence ;
    :contextText "When conflicts are present in the embedded knowledge, the model increasingly relies on externally retrieved knowledge for answers." .

:Qwen1.5-4B :achievesScore "OAR increases from 97.5% to 98.36% at 2:1" ;
    :contextText "with the OAR increasing from 97.5% to 98.36% when the ratio of conflict data is 2:1." .

:Qwen1.5-4B :achievesScore "preference for later conflict 77.52% vs 82.08% with internal conflicts" ;
    :contextText "the model prefers the later-positioned conflict evidence more when internal conflicts are present (77.52% vs. 82.08%)" .

:LLaMA3-70B :achievesScore "MR drops from 67.52% to 8.31% with descriptions" ;
    :contextText "Take LLAMA3-70B as an example, the MRdrops from 67.52% to 8.31% when descriptions are included." .

:Qwen1.5-4B :achievesScore "MR decreases from 55.37% to 41.80% at 2:1 with descriptions" ;
    :contextText "when the internal conflict ratio is 2:1, the MRdecreases from 55.37% to 41.80% with the inclusion of descriptions." .

:DetailedDescriptions :improves :FaithfulnessOfLLMs ;
    :contextText "designing detailed instructions can effectively improve the faithfulness of LLMs." .

